                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12915861" author="tlipcon" created="Tue, 28 Sep 2010 18:14:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you clarify the purpose and management of HBase groups as distinct entities from HDFS groups?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems to me we would like to use the same GroupMappingService interface that HDFS uses, so that by default the groups match up between the systems.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12915873" author="ghelmling" created="Tue, 28 Sep 2010 18:45:47 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It seems to me we would like to use the same GroupMappingService interface that HDFS uses, so that by default the groups match up between the systems.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s definitely the plan for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3025&quot; title=&quot;Coprocessor based simple access control&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3025&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3025&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, where a user&apos;s groups (as resolved by GroupMappingService) can also be used for permission assignments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue proposes adding an additional layer of HBase persisted and manipulated roles, where a role can contain members who are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;users&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;groups&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;other roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This is more akin to PostgreSQL role management.  You could then set say a &quot;webapp&quot; role that has certain access rights to a set of tables and add users or groups as needed.   You can model the same thing with external groups and memberships, but recursive roles give a bit more flexibility to the policy definitions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12915884" author="tlipcon" created="Tue, 28 Sep 2010 19:13:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK. I think it&apos;s a good idea to separate the terminology clearly between &lt;em&gt;roles&lt;/em&gt; (defined and managed as HBase metadata) and &lt;em&gt;groups&lt;/em&gt; (defined and managed by the groups mapping service). Otherwise we are going to have some very confused users.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12915892" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 28 Sep 2010 19:36:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Noted.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13984809" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 29 Apr 2014 21:20:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hadoop group mapping seems good enough for now. Resolving as Later.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
